Product description

Amazon.ca Product Description

Sony MDR7506 Professional Stereo Headphones are ideal for sound monitoring in recording studios, radio, film production, video, electronic news gathering - and virtually any application where high quality sound is required. The closed-ear design MDR-7506 is outrageously popular in pro and home recording studios. It features a rugged design, convenient folding construction, 40mm driver units, gold connectors and a professional-quality OFC (oxygen free copper) cord. Sony 7500 Series headphones offer a practical range of choices for everyone from the casual user to the studio pro. These include the MDR-7506 which is lauded by many professional studios and broadcasters. Features Rugged Design: Proven to be reliable in the toughest situations Folding Construction: Compactness in storage 40mm Driver Unit: For clear, high quality sound reproduction Closed-Ear Design: Comfort and reduction of external noise interference Stereo Unimatch Plug: 1/4 inch and 1/8 inch applications Gold Connectors and OFC Cord: Reliable and stable signal connection and transmission Supplied Soft Case: Protective storage AmericanMusical is an authorized dealer of Sony products.

From the Manufacturer

The Sony MDR-7506 Professional Large Diaphragm Headphone is a large diaphragm foldable headphone designed for professional studio and live/broadcast applications. These large diaphragm, foldable headphones feature a rugged construction, a secure, highly effective closed-ear design, and a 40 millimeter driver unit for clean, clear sound reproduction. The closed-ear design provides both comfort and outstanding reduction of external noises. The included Stereo UniMatch plug allows use in both 1/4-inch and 1/8-inch applications. A soft case for protective storage is included with the headphones.

KenRen
5.0 out of 5 stars The worthiest purchase in headphone less than 300 or 200
Reviewed in Canada on November 8, 2018
Style: HeadphonesVerified Purchase
It is the best monitor headphone in the price, especially after 40 hours of burn-in.

Pros:
1. Very balanced
2. Very clear in sound
3. Very sensitive (Could be too sensitive for non-editing use)
4. Very precise in Bass (not enhanced, but very like a gentle touch)
5. A suitable sound field size for human voice (a bit small for classical music)
6. Very cheap
7. Good isolation from environment sound (Not really noise-canceling, so don't talk them together )
8. Very comfortable (Good for long time of listening)

Cons
1. The cable is definitely not for out doors (I mean it, use it for indoors.)
2. The sound field size are not big enough for some classical music.
3. The earpads were not durable as the headphone, It's skin starts fall after 1 or 2 years of use.
4. Too sensitive and like other professional headphones, you can easily hear the imperfection of some sources.
5. Not really a headphone for gaming, so don't buy it for gaming then blame it.
6. One personal suggestionThe headphone bag they give, were not really helpful and necessary if you are going to carry it around better buy another headphone bag or case.

Better leave comments after 40 or 50 hours of burn-in.
Strongly recommend (Even just for a collection).

Keith
4.0 out of 5 stars Great sound and build quality but a little uncomfortable
Reviewed in Canada on August 30, 2016
Style: HeadphonesVerified Purchase
I bought a pair of these headphone after researching headphones for over a month. I wanted something in the $100-$150 range that sounded nice, was comfortable, didn't bleed noise, and were over-the-ear instead of on ear.
I had read reviews saying that these headphones are extremely well balanced when it comes to sound - bass is not over powering, mids and highs sounds great. I've owned them for a month and a half now and after a lot of listening to music on it, I concur with those reviews. The sound is indeed very good. Much better than comparable headphones from Beats, Bose, Monster, and other such manufacturers. If you haven't owned a good professional-type headphones before, you will notice with these that your songs sound different because you can actually hear a lot of little things that get missed out on many other consumer headphones. So overall, for sound, I really like it and it is more than worth the price.

In terms of comfort, these are not quite over-the-ear headphones but they are certainly bigger than on-ear headphones. So they are good compromise in that terms. I did find, however, that wearing them for even an hour or so started to not just hurt my ears but give me a headache. This is mostly due to the fact that they fit tight to isolate the sound better - which it does a good job of. I decided to wait a few weeks to see if the headphones loosen up a little bit from being used regularly - which they did but I still can't wear them for longer than, at most, 2 hours at a time without getting a headache and having my ears hurt from the strong clamping of the ear cups. So if you want a pair of headphones for long sessions of comfortable listening, these may not be for you.

In terms of style and build quality, I like them. They don't look attention-seeking, but rather, they have that understated tone to them. I personally quite like the look compared to Beats, for example. I personally like having the coiled cable as you can easily move around without worrying about pulling the cable. Which brings me to a little complaint about it - non replaceable cables. The cable is fixed and cannot be replaced. So if you yank it hard and break it, you'll have to send it in for repair. However, with the coiled cable, I think that would be a little harder to do. The weigh a little heavier than I expected but still not too heavy. I like the thinner headband, which is quite surprisingly comfortable.

Packaging is good and easy to open as well. The headphones come with a 3.5mm to 1/4" adapter as well that screws onto the 3.5mm end of the headphone's cable.

So overall, this is my verdict:
Pros:
-Great sound quality
-Well priced
-Good sound isolation
-Coiled cable helps prevent breaking the cable
-Good build quality

Cons:
-Uncomfortable
-Non-replaceable cable

Dewi
5.0 out of 5 stars Studio Sound Without Breaking the Bank
Reviewed in the United Kingdom on January 7, 2024
Style: HeadphonesVerified Purchase
How they surprised me:

- Studio-quality sound for under 100: I didn't expect headphones this affordable to sound this good. The clarity, accuracy, and detail are on par with much more expensive options.

- Comfortable enough for long listening sessions: I spend hours working and listening to music with these headphones, and they never get uncomfortable. The lightweight design and soft ear cups are a lifesaver.

- Durable build that inspires confidence: These headphones feel like they can take a beating. The sturdy construction and high-quality materials give me peace of mind knowing they'll last.
